trans-unit.source: PowerShell CmdLets to manage the BizTalk Service
trans-unit.target: PowerShell CmdLets to manage the BizTalk Service

trans-unit.source: This section lists the PowerShell cmdlets for management operations on <token>af_integration</token>.
trans-unit.target: This section lists the PowerShell cmdlets for management operations on <token>af_integration</token>.

trans-unit.source: <token>af_integration</token> also provides PowerShell cmdlets for managing <token>lobconnect</token>.
trans-unit.target: <token>af_integration</token> also provides PowerShell cmdlets for managing <token>lobconnect</token>.

trans-unit.source: See <link xlink:href="10873203-56b3-445c-8340-ef073f5365f8" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Installing the Azure BizTalk Services SDK - June 2013 Preview</link> for instructions.
trans-unit.target: See <link xlink:href="10873203-56b3-445c-8340-ef073f5365f8" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Installing the Azure BizTalk Services SDK - June 2013 Preview</link> for instructions.

trans-unit.source: Open the PowerShell window with administrator privileges.
trans-unit.target: Open the PowerShell window with administrator privileges.

trans-unit.source: Run <embeddedLabel>import-module</embeddedLabel> to import the <token>af_integration</token> module to the current session.
trans-unit.target: Run <embeddedLabel>import-module</embeddedLabel> to import the <token>af_integration</token> module to the current session.

trans-unit.source: When using <legacyBold>import-module</legacyBold>, modules exist only when the PowerShell command window is open; which is the current PowerShell session.
trans-unit.target: When using <legacyBold>import-module</legacyBold>, modules exist only when the PowerShell command window is open; which is the current PowerShell session.

trans-unit.source: When the PowerShell command window is closed, the session is closed and the module is removed.
trans-unit.target: When the PowerShell command window is closed, the session is closed and the module is removed.

trans-unit.source: If you used these PowerShell cmdlets in the Preview release of the <token>af_integration_full</token> SDK to build PowerShell scripts, you must update those to include the right import path.
trans-unit.target: If you used these PowerShell cmdlets in the Preview release of the <token>af_integration_full</token> SDK to build PowerShell scripts, you must update those to include the right import path.

trans-unit.source: You can download <externalLink><linkText>Azure BizTalk Service Management Sample</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=335967</linkUri></externalLink> that demonstrates how to use the PowerShell cmdlets.
trans-unit.target: You can download <externalLink><linkText>Azure BizTalk Service Management Sample</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=335967</linkUri></externalLink> that demonstrates how to use the PowerShell cmdlets.

trans-unit.source: It also demonstrates use of some sample cmdlets that can be used for backing up and restoring <token>af_integration</token>, retrieving <token>af_integration</token> properties, and syncing <token>ac2</token> keys.
trans-unit.target: It also demonstrates use of some sample cmdlets that can be used for backing up and restoring <token>af_integration</token>, retrieving <token>af_integration</token> properties, and syncing <token>ac2</token> keys.
